HEADWORD: Sanctiloquent
<hw>Sanc*til"o*quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sanctus</ets> holy + <ets>loquens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>loqui</ets>
to speak.]</ety> <def>Discoursing on heavenly or holy things, or in a
holy manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sanctimonial</ent>⟦br⟧
